“Friendship isn’t about whom you’ve known the longest…it’s about who came and never left your side.”

That said, she IS the friend I’ve known the longest.  The one who asked me to be her best friend at 12-years-old and never looked back. She knows my heart and I know hers.  We share enough secrets, moments and memories to last a lifetime.  She’s the best friend a girl could ask for and I’m so thankful she’s mine. 
🤍

😘🤍🎉

My aunt set out on a 30-day painting journey in the desert of Arizona.  She completed a 6x8 canvas every day for 30-days and posted them to her Facebook page.  I couldn’t wait for her posts each day to see what incredible scene she had to share next.  I knew immediately I needed some of these pieces in my home and she graciously brought every painting over for a private showcase. Twenty-five painting purchases later, I finally have some of them on display.  They are unique and beautiful and she has a story about every scene/location.  I couldn’t be more proud to display her artwork in my home and to share her talent and our love of the Arizona landscape. 🤍🤍

We have a TON of bougainvillea on this property and although it’s messy, I love it so much!  It’s reminiscent of rose petals when it’s scattered all over the ground and adds such a beautiful element of color and whimsy to our desert terrain. 🌺 
That said, bougainvillea in the pool-slightly annoying. 🤣🤪

And just like that middle school basketball has come to an end for Jackson. You feel like you have all the time in the world to enjoy your kids and then all of a sudden you’re celebrating an ending. We are a basketball loving family and this kiddo truly caught the basketball bug.  His commitment and dedication to being the best he can possibly be started years ago.  We’ve watched him continually strive to improve, never giving up when he faced a challenge.  He ended his 8th grade season with 292 pts and the honor of being named MVP (voted on by his awesome teammates). We are eager to continue watching his growth as a player, a teammate and an all-around awesome young man. 🏀 🤍 
**Last two videos are 2017/2018.  So fun to see how far he’s come.

Felt so good pulling spaces together again. We’ve taken things slow with this house and our first renovation (backyard) is almost complete.  I couldn’t wait to set up all the new furniture bringing these new areas to life. 
❤️☀️🌵

Lake Tahoe- a MUST visit vacation destination! 
Our near town accommodations at @gondolavista were perfection.  We could walk to everything, the home was well equipped and I could see spending either a summer or winter vacation in this location. We took an hour long trail ride with @zephyr_cove_stable that ended with beautiful views of the lake. Spent a couple hours at Sand Harbor (which could have easily been half a day or more for me). Boated and tubed on the lake (kids actually got in the 59 degree water) and enjoyed beautiful views in Emerald Bay.  Ended our experience with @olddominionmusic in concert at @harveystahoe for the incredible “No Bad Vibes” tour.  It was fun for the whole family and a place we’ve decided needs to become annual.  Until next time, Tahoe! 🫶

AZ --> CA 4th of July Week

We had never driven from AZ to CA and the drive was unexpectedly interesting.  Not much in between, but the changing landscape was enough to keep us entertained. Sand dunes to rocky mountain ranges and a glimpse of the boarder wall kept us searching throughout the car ride. A stop in Yuma, AZ offered a chance meeting with our new friend, Jimmy, who had stories for days about his old times in Branson, MO recording music with legends. 

A beautiful stay at @delcoronado (which you know I loved) was a highlight!  What’s not to love about a building from the late 1800s.  My daughter, a girl after my own heart, asked to do the ghost tour, which of course I agreed to.  The town of Coronado bleeds patriotism over the 4th and the pride they have in their parade is overflowing and contagious. 
Our one room hotel fit our family of six, but you better believe I was ready for our next stop (to enjoy some separation) once we hit Mission Beach.  Great friends showed us around in both places and even prepared the fish the boys caught for meals each evening. From fire pits and s’mores, to picnics in the park, to beach days, a trip to Seaworld and countless hours in the water, we had an epic trip. 🤍

A few days with my best girls was good for the mind, body and soul. 
We flew into LAX and drove up the coast.  First stop was @malibufarm for breakfast with view and a little shopping at @aviatornation.  Continued north for a two night stay in Santa Barbara at @hotelcalifornian . The hotel, the architecture, the lush plants- Santa Barbara is simply stunning.  Dinner the first night in the funk zone was my favorite with shared plates at @thelarksb. The following day we walked the pier, enjoyed breakfast over looking the beach at @jeanninesrestaurants and had an incredible lunch at @sanysidroranch . Needed hours at this place to take in the lush grounds and every inch of Montecito.  We left Santa Barbara for Santa Monica and a one night stay at @properhotels . On the way we made a quick shopping stop at the Malibu Country Mart, which ended up being a real treat as we caught a glimpse of Sir Anthony Hopkins at lunch. 😍. Finished the trip with rooftop dinner at a Santa Monica hot spot- @elephante 
It was a trip to remember with my best girls!  Over 20 years of friendship, 8 kids between us, an over abundance of experiences and memories; I can’t imagine life without these two! 🤍🤍

My sweet 10 year old girl wanted her ears pierced for her birthday.  She was patient and waited until after our family vacation and today was the day!  We had the best experience at @heyrowan .  The nurses and staff were kind and welcoming and we sure loved our nurse Tousha!  She didn’t rush us, was patient and explained every step so perfectly to Vivian.  A special day for my special girl. 💕
